headline: Occidental earnings, FOMC minutes, housing data: What to Watch
summary: Asking for a Trend Host Josh Lipton previews several of the biggest stories to come tomorrow, Wednesday, February 18, including Carvana (CVNA), Occidental Petroleum (OXY), and Booking Holdings (BKNG); the minutes from the Federal Reserve's January FOMC meeting; and the latest data on US housing starts and building permits. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Asking for a Trend.

headline: Winter Wonders: Agoda's Search Insights Unveil South Korea's Winter Appeal among Inbound Travelers
summary: Despite the ongoing cold winter season, South Korea continues to attract interest from inbound travelers, fueled by a variety of seasonal events and activities available during the winter months. Reflecting this trend, digital travel platform Agoda has revealed the most searched destinations and preferred winter activities among international travelers visiting South Korea.

headline: Route 66 Partnership Puts Booking Holdings Valuation And Growth In Focus
summary: Booking.com, part of Booking Holdings (NasdaqGS:BKNG), has been named Official Travel Partner of the Route 66 Centennial. The partnership covers Route 66 centennial celebrations planned across multiple U.S. states throughout 2026. The collaboration ties Booking.com's brand and services to a yearlong Americana travel event aimed at U.S. and international visitors.
